<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                    <head>125. Letter From the Ambassador at Large (<persName corresp="#p_TLET1" type="from">Thompson</persName>) to the Assistant Secretary of Defense
                        for International Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_MNJT1" type="to">McNaughton</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d125fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 31–1 <gloss target="#t_GER1">GER</gloss> E–US.
                            Secret.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1965-07-17">July 17, 1965</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Dear <persName>John</persName>:</p>
                    <p>The Secretary has carefully considered the points mentioned in Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>’s letter of April
                            fifth,<note n="2" xml:id="d125fn2">Not printed.</note> regarding the
                        flight of United States helicopters over East Berlin. He has decided that we
                        ought not to resume helicopter flights at this time. In light of his
                        decision, I am sending to you for <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>
                        concurrence a draft joint State-Defense message.2</p>
                    <p>Sincerely,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName>
                                <hi rend="strong">Tommy</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>